e, or each full round in an action scene, the shared&nbsp; Momentum pool decreases by 1 point</span> &nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Success at a Cost</h1>\n<p>Basic level of success even if the Test is failed (GM’s choice)</p>\n<p>No Momentum gained (even bonus Momentum) &nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"G6sEWWuxObpRANBM","name":"Actions","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"b3GqfKX5F9CV6QNC","sort":500001,"flags":{},"content":"<h2>Taking Action</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>The gamemaster and player determine the relevant SKILL and the DIFFICULTY.</li>\n<li>Difficulty determines the number of SUCCESSES required to perform the action.</li>\n<li>SKILL EXPERTISE is added to the base ATTRIBUTE to determine the TARGET NUMBER (TN).</li>\n<li>Roll 2d20, counting each die rolled separately.</li>\n<li>Each roll equal to or less than the TN is a success.</li>\n<li>Players can roll additional d20s by generating DOOM, spending MOMENTUM, or using RESOURCES.</li>\n<li>A roll equal to or under the SKILL FOCUS is worth two successes.</li>\n<li>Any extra successes become MOMENTUM.</li>\n<li>No more than three additional d20s may be rolled for one test.</li>\n<li>Some TALENTS allow additional dice, or re-rolls, automatic successes, or generate additional Momentum.</li>\n<li>Results of 20 cause COMPLICATIONS. A skill test for an untrained skill becomes a Complication on a 19 or 20. &nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Available actions</h2>\n<table style=\"float: left; height: 391px;\">\n<thead>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 122px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-align: center;\">Standard Action</span></td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 772px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-align: center;\">Eﬀect</span></td>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 51px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 51px; width: 122px;\"><strong>Limitation</strong></td>\n<td style=\"height: 51px; width: 772px;\"><strong>1 per Turn; <br>1 extra for 1 Fortune, <br>2 Momentum (+1 Difficulty) or 1 Momentum while Dual Wielding (+1 Difficulty)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 122px;\">Assist</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 772px;\">Roll only 1D20 with their appropriate Skill; if the leader scores at least one success on the roll, any successes generated are<br>added to the leader’s total.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 122px;\">Attack</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 772px;\">Melee Attack = Melee Skill (1 adjusted by Reach); Ranged Attack = Ranged Weapon Skill (1 adjusted by Range); Threaten Attack<br>= Persuade (1 adjusted by Range)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 122px;\">Brace</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 772px;\">Remove the Unwieldy quality of a weapon (which generates Complication on 19-20); lose Brace if the character moves</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 122px;\">Charge</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 772px;\">Animal Handling (1+1 for every point the target’s Reach is longer than the rider’s weapon) to make an attack; may spend<br>Momentum to: gain +1d20 and +1[CD] to the attack, add Knockback quality and/or make the mount’s attack</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 122px;\">Exploit</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 772px;\">Observation (1) to find weaknesses; next attack gains Piercing 2; may spend 1 Momentum to add 1d20 and +1[CD] to next attack<br>(repeatable, but max 5d20 rolled)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 122px;\">Gallop</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 772px;\">Animal Handling (1) to move within Medium range +1 area per Momentum spent; +2 Difficulty to all Skill Tests</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 122px;\">Pass</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 772px;\">Do nothing on your Turn</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 122px;\">Ready</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 772px;\">Delay Standard Acton until a triggering condition</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 122px;\">Recover</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 772px;\">Resistance (1) to recover 2 Vigor or Discipline (1) to recover 2 Resolve; + 2 more points for each Momentum spent (Repeatable);<br>may reroll any Cover or Morale Dice until the start of the next turn</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 122px;\">Skill Test</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 772px;\">Attempt a Skill Test</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 122px;\">Sprint</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 772px;\">Move within Long range (2 Area away); +1 Difficulty to all Skill Tests except Defense Reaction</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 122px;\">Treatment</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 772px;\">Healing (1) to recover 3 Vigor or Counsel (1) to recover 3 Resolve someone within Reach; + 3 more points for each Momentum<br>spent (Repeatable); may recover Resolve with +1 Difficulty for each Distance beyond Reach</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 122px;\">Withdraw</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 772px;\">Leave enemy’s Reach without Retaliate (Free Acton if enemy is outnumbered)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"float: left;\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 121px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-align: center;\">Minor Action</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 773px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-align: center;\">Eﬀect</span></td>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 121px;\"><strong>Limitation</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 773px;\"><strong>1 per Turn (may exchange the Standard to gain an&nbsp;additional&nbsp;Minor Acton)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 121px;\">Canter</td>\n<td style=\"width: 773px;\">Move within Long range (2 Area away) on horseback; +1 Difficulty to all Skill Tests except Defense Reaction; attacks against<br>character and his mount are +1 Difficulty</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 121px;\">Clear</td>\n<td style=\"width: 773px;\">Remove a status eﬀect or problem; Appropriate Skill Test of Difficulty 2 or the rating of the status</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 121px;\">Draw Item</td>\n<td style=\"width: 773px;\">Pick up an item within reach or draw a weapon</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 121px;\">Mount/Dismount</td>\n<td style=\"width: 773px;\">Gets into or out of horseback</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 121px;\">Movement</td>\n<td style=\"width: 773px;\">Move (or Trot while mounted) within Medium range (1 Area away)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 121px;\">Regain Guard</td>\n<td style=\"width: 773px;\">Parry Test with a Difficulty equal to the highest Reach of the weapons wielded by any enemies within Reach</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 121px;\">Stand</td>\n<td style=\"width: 773px;\">Stand up from Prone (cannot be performed on the same Turn than Drop Prone)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"float: left;\">\n<thead>\n<tr style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<th style=\"width: 121px;\">Free Action</th>\n<th style=\"width: 777px;\">Eﬀect</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 119px;\"><strong>Limitation</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 775px;\"><strong>As many as possible (each MAY be performed only once per Turn)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 119px;\">Adjust</td>\n<td style=\"width: 775px;\">Move within Close range (same Area)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 119px;\">Drop Item</td>\n<td style=\"width: 775px;\">Drop a single item held in one or both hands</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 119px;\">Drop Prone</td>\n<td style=\"width: 775px;\">Gain 2[CD] Cover; +1 Difficulty on attack from medium range or further and 2 Momentum on attacks from Close range against the<br>character</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 119px;\">Simple Task</td>\n<td style=\"width: 775px;\">Any task of Difficulty 0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 119px;\">Speak</td>\n<td style=\"width: 775px;\">Talk, war cry or shout a few words (cannot be used to attempt a Test)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 106px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-align: center;\">Reaction</span></td>\n<td style=\"width: 788px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-align: center;\">Eﬀect</span></td>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 106px;\"><strong>Limitation</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 788px;\"><strong>First in a Turn cost 1 Doom; second, 2 Doom; third ,3 Doom...</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 106px;\">Defend</td>\n<td style=\"width: 788px;\">Melee Attack = Parry Skill (struggle); Ranged Attack = Acrobatics Skill (struggle); Threaten Attack = Discipline (struggle); while<br>mounted, use Animal Handling with assistance of the mount’s Acrobatics or character’s Acrobatics and take 3 [CD] &nbsp;for falling</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 106px;\">Protect</td>\n<td style=\"width: 788px;\">Melee Attack = Parry Skill (2); Ranged Attack = Acrobatics Skill (2); Threaten Attack = Discipline (2) to become the target of the<br>attack and Momentum scored is used to determine if the attack is successful</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 106px;\">Retaliate</td>\n<td style=\"width: 788px;\">Make a melee attack against an enemy leaving Reach or attempting a non-attack Skill Test within Reach</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"HCpky6wqyxSIdaUt","name":"Dazed","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"fitw9XwkJ1H7s1wk","sort":300001,"flags":{},"content":"<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">+1 Difficulty to all skill tests until the Dazed condition ends</p>"}
{"_id":"JVSpyycIKgp3UGX3","name":"Displays of Power","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"b3GqfKX5F9CV6QNC","sort":600001,"flags":{},"content":"<h1>TO BE SPLIT INTO SEPARATE WEAPON ENTRIES,</h1>\n<h1>Cost of 0, Avail 0</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"height: 696px;\">\n<thead>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<th style=\"width: 163px; height: 16px;\">Name</th>\n<th style=\"width: 112px; height: 16px;\">Skill</th>\n<th style=\"width: 73px; height: 16px;\">Range</th>\n<th style=\"width: 68px; height: 16px;\">Damage</th>\n<th style=\"width: 358px; height: 16px;\">Qualites</th>\n<th style=\"width: 175px; height: 16px;\">Requirement</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 85px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 161px; height: 85px;\">A Mighty Name</td>\n<td style=\"width: 110px; height: 85px;\">Command<br>or<br>Discipline</td>\n<td style=\"width: 71px; height: 85px;\">Close</td>\n<td style=\"width: 66px; height: 85px;\">X [CD]</td>\n<td style=\"width: 356px; height: 85px;\">Area: The attack automatically aﬀects any target within Reach of the initial target, and then one additional target within Close range for each Eﬀect rolled, starting with the next closest target</td>\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 85px;\">Min. Renown 3; X = Renown</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 102px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 161px; height: 102px;\">Dead Man’s Stare</td>\n<td style=\"width: 110px; height: 102px;\">Melee</td>\n<td style=\"width: 71px; height: 102px;\">Close</td>\n<td style=\"width: 66px; height: 102px;\">3 [CD]</td>\n<td style=\"width: 356px; height: 102px;\">\n<p>Area: The attack automatcally aﬀects any target within Reach of the inital target, and then one additonal target within Close range for each Eﬀect rolled, starting with the next closest target.</p>\n<p>Vicious 1: +1 damage for each Eﬀect rolled</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 102px;\">Head of a Toughened or<br>Nemesis likked during the<br>Scene</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 68px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 161px; height: 68px;\">Flaming Brand</td>\n<td style=\"width: 110px; height: 68px;\">Survival</td>\n<td style=\"width: 71px; height: 68px;\">Close</td>\n<td style=\"width: 66px; height: 68px;\">3&nbsp;[CD]</td>\n<td style=\"width: 356px; height: 68px;\">\n<p>Stun: inﬂict Staggered Conditon if one or more Eﬀects are rolled; may ignore at the cost of 1 Doom per Eﬀect rolled</p>\n<p>Vicious 1: +1 damage for each Eﬀect rolled</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 68px;\">Object bearing a large and<br>open ﬂame</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 136px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 161px; height: 136px;\">Impossible Feat of<br>Might</td>\n<td style=\"width: 110px; height: 136px;\">Athletics</td>\n<td style=\"width: 71px; height: 136px;\">Medium</td>\n<td style=\"width: 66px; height: 136px;\">5&nbsp;[CD]</td>\n<td style=\"width: 356px; height: 136px;\">\n<p>Area: The atack automatcally aﬀects any target within Reach of the inital target, and then one additonal target within Close range for each Eﬀect rolled, starting with the next closest target</p>\n<p>Stun: inﬂict Staggered Conditon if one or more Eﬀects are rolled; may ignore at the cost of 1 Doom per Eﬀect rolled</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 136px;\">Perform a grand feat of<br>strength prior or as part of<br>this acton</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 68px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 161px; height: 68px;\">Knife to the Throat</td>\n<td style=\"width: 110px; height: 68px;\">Melee or<br>Stealth</td>\n<td style=\"width: 71px; height: 68px;\">Reach</td>\n<td style=\"width: 66px; height: 68px;\">4&nbsp;[CD]</td>\n<td style=\"width: 356px; height: 68px;\">\n<p>Stun: inﬂict Staggered Conditon if one or more Eﬀects are rolled; may ignore at the cost of 1 Doom per Eﬀect rolled</p>\n<p>Vicious 1: +1 damage for each Eﬀect rolled</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 68px;\">A sharp blade held against a<br>previously unaware foe</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 102px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 161px; height: 102px;\">Sorcerous Might</td>\n<td style=\"width: 110px; height: 102px;\">Sorcery</td>\n<td style=\"width: 71px; height: 102px;\">Medium</td>\n<td style=\"width: 66px; height: 102px;\">5&nbsp;[CD]</td>\n<td style=\"width: 356px; height: 102px;\">Area: The atack automatcally aﬀects any target within Reach of the inital target, and then one additonal target within Close range for each Eﬀect rolled, starting with the next closest target<br>Intense: +1 harm if harm is inﬂicted</td>\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 102px;\">The character must have cast<br>a spell during the current<br>scene, and must have been<br>seen to do so.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 85px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 161px; height: 85px;\">Stain the Soil Red</td>\n<td style=\"width: 110px; height: 85px;\">Melee or<br>Ranged<br>Weapons</td>\n<td style=\"width: 71px; height: 85px;\">Close</td>\n<td style=\"width: 66px; height: 85px;\">X&nbsp;[CD]</td>\n<td style=\"width: 356px; height: 85px;\">Area: The atack automatcally aﬀects any target within Reach of the inital target, and then one additonal target within Close range for each Eﬀect rolled, startng with the next closest target</td>\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 85px;\">Have personally slain 3 or<br>more enemies during the<br>Scene; X = number of<br>enemies slain</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 161px; height: 34px;\">Steely Glare</td>\n<td style=\"width: 110px; height: 34px;\">Persuade</td>\n<td style=\"width: 71px; height: 34px;\">Close</td>\n<td style=\"width: 66px; height: 34px;\">2&nbsp;[CD]</td>\n<td style=\"width: 356px; height: 34px;\">Stun: inﬂict Staggered Conditon if one or more Eﬀects are rolled; may ignore at the cost of 1 Doom per Eﬀect rolled.</td>\n<td style=\"width: 173px; height: 34px;\">None (Basic Atack)<br><br></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"Lb2Hl427COMGIgiL","name":"Attack Sequence","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"b3GqfKX5F9CV6QNC","sort":100001,"flags":{},"content":"<h2>Declare the Attack</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>&nbsp;Choose attack type: MELEE, RANGED, or THREATEN.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Choose attack TARGET.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Choose a WEAPON (for Melee and Ranged attack) or a METHOD of scaring the target (for a Threaten attack).</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Target chooses whether or not to make a DEFENSE Reaction.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Make a Skill Test</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Attacker makes a SKILL TEST to attack: AVERAGE (D1), or a STRUGGLE if target takes a Defense Reaction.</li>\n<li>If the skill test or Struggle fails or is defeated in the Struggle, the attack ends.</li>\n<li>If the attacker succeeds, then the attacker rolls DAMAGE.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Roll Damage</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Roll COMBAT DICE&sect;based on the attack type and bonus damage.</li>\n<li>Each 1 or 2 rolled applies that much DAMAGE.</li>\n<li>Each 5 or 6 rolled creates an EFFECT and deals 1 damage. Effects activate QUALITIES.</li>\n<li>Qualities might cause additional damage or other conditions.</li>\n<li>Momentum can be spent to increase damage by +1 per point.</li>\n<li>Total the damage.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Armor and Soak</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>The defender determines SOAK when damage is determined.</li>\n<li>Soak is a combination of fi xed value (from Armor or Courage) and dice (Cover and Morale).</li>\n<li>Roll any Soak and add the total rolled to the fi xed value.</li>\n<li>Reduce Soak by any eff ects rolled by the PIERCING Quality.</li>\n<li>The result is the character&rsquo;s total Soak.</li>\n<li>Subtract Soak from the attack&rsquo;s damage.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Stress and Harm</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Any damage remaining is removed from STRESS.</li>\n<li>Remove physical damage from VIGOR, mental from RESOLVE.</li>\n<li>For every 5 points of Stress, the target takes 1 HARM.</li>\n<li>Remove physical Harm from WOUNDS, mental from TRAUMA.</li>\n<li>If the target has 0 Vigor or Resolve, the target takes 1 Harm.</li>\n</ol>"}
{"_id":"Ly7xKV4HIKyaA8O7","name":"Staggered","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"fitw9XwkJ1H7s1wk","sort":700001,"flags":{},"content":"<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">Can only perform a Standard Acton in a turn if the player is willing to pay 1 point of Doom;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">Cannot perform a Reaction unless spending 1 Fortune point in addition to the reaction&rsquo;s normal Doom cost.</p>"}
{"_id":"PnKW6EuB2KZPMUeP","name":"Burning X","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"fitw9XwkJ1H7s1wk","sort":200001,"flags":{},"content":"<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">Condition lasts for a number of rounds equal to number of Effects rolled (if no effects were rolled, the cause of the burning effect will list a duration);</p>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">at the end of the target’s turn, X? physical and mental damage (roll once and apply it to both), ignoring Armor Soak (Effects rolled increase the number of rounds);</p>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">Clear Minor Acton to remove this effect (prone character can spend a Standard Action rolling around, and reduces the Difficulty by 2)</p>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"TZl359i2411Hu4Io","name":"Stress & Harm Recovery","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"b3GqfKX5F9CV6QNC","sort":700001,"flags":{},"content":"<h1>Health</h1>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 93px;\">Damage Type</td>\n<td style=\"width: 146px;\">Stress</td>\n<td style=\"width: 91px;\">Soak</td>\n<td style=\"width: 268px;\">Harm</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88px;\">Recovery (Self)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 102px;\">Recovery (Others)</td>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 93px;\">Physical (Creature)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 146px;\">Vigor<br>(Brawn + Resistance)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 91px;\">Armor (static) <br>+ Cover (dice)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 268px;\">Wound<br>(Agility, Brawn, Coordination)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88px;\">Resistance</td>\n<td style=\"width: 102px;\">Healing</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 93px;\">Physical (Object)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 146px;\">Structure</td>\n<td style=\"width: 91px;\">Armor (static)<br>+ Cover (dice)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 268px;\">Break<br>(Any test involving structure)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88px;\">&nbsp;<strong>-</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 102px;\">Crafts</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 93px;\">Mental</td>\n<td style=\"width: 146px;\">Resolve<br>(Willpower + Discipline)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 91px;\">Courage (static)<br>+ Morale (dice)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 268px;\">Trauma<br>(Awareness, Intelligence, Personality, Willpower)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 88px;\">Discipline</td>\n<td style=\"width: 102px;\">Counsel</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Effects of Harm</h2>\n<p>For each untreated harm, the character has checks for corresponding attributes &amp; skills increased by one.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>For each Wound, the DC of Agility, Brawn, Coordination and their linked skills increases by one.</li>\n<li>For each Trauma, the DC of Awareness, Intelligence, Personality, Willpower and their linked skills increases by one.</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>Recovery In Combat</h1>\n<h2>Stress</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>A successful Healing check (DC = number of Wounds, minimum of 1) heals&nbsp; 3 point of Vigor+ 3 more per momentum spent additionnaly.</li>\n<li>A successful Counsel check (DC = number of Trauma, minimum of 1) heals 3 point of Resolve + 3 more per momentum spent additionnaly.</li>\n<li>Resolve can be restored at range by increasing the difficulty by 1 per distance step.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Harm</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Harms cannot be treated in combat and req</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>Recovery Out of combat</h1>\n<h2>Stress</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>All Stress (Vigor and Resolve) is recovered at the end of an action scene.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Harm</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>To treat Harm (either Wounds &amp; Trauma): make an appropriate Skill Test (D1) to treat 1 Harm,+ 1 more points for each Momentum spent (Repeatable)</li>\n<li>Treated Harm is latent: If a character suﬀers a new Harm of that type, any treated Harms immediately return as Wounds&nbsp;or Trauma, reopening under strain.</li>\n<li>To heal Harm: spend time and Gold during Carousing &nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>Exhaustion</h1>\n<h2>Fatigue</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Accumulates through physical exertion: Cold, Heat, Thrist, Starvation, Forced March, Sleep Deprivation, etc.</li>\n<li>Each point of Fatigue reduces the maximum vigor of the character. If Vigor is reduce to 0, the character falls unconscious. Further fatigue kills the character.</li>\n<li>After removing the source of the fatigue and 8 hours of rest, you can attemp an Average (D1) Resistance test, sucess removes 1 point of&nbsp; fatigue + 1 additionnal point per momentum spent.</li>\n<li>Source: Core Book p. 79</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Despair</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Accumulates through complications on discipline tests and in other negative situations.</li>\n<li>Each point of Despair reduces the maximum Resolve of the character. If Resolved is reduced to 0, the character gives up; unwilling to continue on. Further Despair will cause the character to lose the will to live, becoming insensate/comatose forever.</li>\n<li>After a comforting situation that revives the spirit and 8 hours of rest, you can attempt an Average (D1) Discipline test, success remove 1 point of despair +1 additionnal point per momentum spent.</li>\n<li>Source: Core Book p. 66</li>\n</ul>"}
{"_id":"UgaTFiL5c6muef4N","name":"Carousing","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"b3GqfKX5F9CV6QNC","sort":900001,"flags":{},"content":"<h2>S&eacute;quence de festivit&eacute;s</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Qui festoie ?</li>\n<li>Upkeep</li>\n<li>Activities</li>\n<li>Events</li>\n<li>Regroup</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Qui festoie? (grouping)</h2>\n<p>Est-ce que vous bris&eacute;s le groupe ou est-ce que vous festoyez ensemble ou en sous-groupes ?</p>\n<h2>Maintenance (upkeep)</h2>\n<p>Le&nbsp;co&ucirc;t de la maintenance&nbsp;de votre niveau de vie est de&nbsp;3&nbsp;pi&egrave;ce d'or&nbsp;+ [votre standing social] - [votre renom]. Ne descends jamais dans le n&eacute;gatif, au mieux le co&ucirc;t est de 0 pi&egrave;ce d'or.</p>\n<p>Dans le cas o&ugrave; vous ne pouvez pas payer la maintenance, la difficult&eacute; de tous les jets de Commandement, Persuasion et Soci&eacute;t&eacute; de la prochaine partie sera augment&eacute;e par 1 pour chaque pi&egrave;ce d'or&nbsp;non pay&eacute;.</p>\n<h2>Activit&eacute;s (activities)</h2>\n<p>Vous devrez d&eacute;crire ce que votre personnage fait pendant la p&eacute;riode de festoiement, par courriel, verbalement sur Roll20 ou dans l'article du forum pour la partie qui vient d'&ecirc;tre compl&eacute;t&eacute;e.</p>\n<h3>Rencontrer un Patron</h3>\n<p>Co&ucirc;te 10 pi&egrave;ce d'or pour rencontrer un nouveau patron.</p>\n<p>Co&ucirc;te 5 pi&egrave;ce d'or&nbsp;pour rencontrer un patron existant.</p>\n<p>Ce co&ucirc;t est diminu&eacute; par la position sociale et le renom, il peut &ecirc;tre rentable de rencontrer un patron. Possible de diminuer le co&ucirc;t de la rencontre dans le n&eacute;gatif.</p>\n<h3>&Eacute;changer</h3>\n<p>Payer en pi&egrave;ces d'or le co&ucirc;t de l'objet qui sera produit sur mesure lorsque pertinent.</p>\n<p>La m&eacute;canique de recherche et achat d'objet en Core p.135 peut &ecirc;tre utilis&eacute; en remplacement. La m&eacute;canique de vente d'objets en Core p.136 peut &ecirc;tre utilis&eacute;e pour se d&eacute;lester d'objets.</p>\n<h3>Parier &amp; Jouer</h3>\n<p>Miser au moins 1 pi&egrave;ce d'or, lancer 1&nbsp;Combat Dice&nbsp;pour chaque pi&egrave;ce d'or mis&eacute;.</p>\n<p>Pour tricher, le joueur ajoute +1 or pour chaque effet roul&eacute;. S'il y a plus d'effets que de rang d'expertise en vol, le personnage est pris en flagrant delis: tout l'or est perdu, une complication survient et la r&eacute;putation de tricheur s'&eacute;tends.</p>\n<h3>Rumeurs</h3>\n<p>D&eacute;penser au moins 1 pi&egrave;ce d'or, lancer 1&nbsp;Combat Dice&nbsp;pour chaque pi&egrave;ce d'or d&eacute;pens&eacute;. Le total roul&eacute; repr&eacute;sente le nombre de rumeurs entendues. Pour chaque effet roul&eacute;, le personnage entend une information importante. Un joueur peu rerouller un Combat Dice pour chaque rang d'expertise en persuasion.</p>\n<h3>R&eacute;cup&eacute;rer</h3>\n<p>Pour&nbsp;chaque dommage subis, le co&ucirc;t est d'1 pi&egrave;ce d'or&nbsp;(Blessure, Traumatisme, D&eacute;sespoir et Fatigue), Poison et Maladie.</p>\n<p>Un personnage avec 3 rangs d'expertise de gu&eacute;rison peut gu&eacute;rir les dommages physiques et 2 rang d'expertise de conseil pour les dommages psychologiques. Le co&ucirc;t en pi&egrave;ces d'or est r&eacute;duit de 1 par personnage additionnel ayant conseil ou gu&eacute;rison avec une expertise de 2+.</p>\n<h3>Cultiver votre Renom</h3>\n<p>D&eacute;penser au moins 1 pi&egrave;ce d'or, lancer 1&nbsp;Combat Dice&nbsp;pour chaque pi&egrave;ce d'or&nbsp;d&eacute;pens&eacute;. Si le total d&eacute;passe ou &eacute;galise le renom actuel, le renom augmente de un.&nbsp;</p>\n<h4>Probl&egrave;mes (troubles)</h4>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Effets roul&eacute;s</td>\n<td>Exemples de probl&egrave;mes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1-2&nbsp;</td>\n<td>1 pi&egrave;ces d'or&nbsp;de plus pour r&eacute;parer les d&eacute;g&acirc;ts.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3-4&nbsp;</td>\n<td>2&nbsp;pi&egrave;ces d'or&nbsp;de plus pour r&eacute;parer les d&eacute;g&acirc;ts.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5+&nbsp;</td>\n<td>3&nbsp;pi&egrave;ces d'or&nbsp;de plus pour r&eacute;parer les d&eacute;g&acirc;ts, perte d'un point de renom. Pour chaque effet suppl&eacute;mentaires apr&egrave;s 5, le co&ucirc;t des amendes et pots-de-vin augmente de 1 or.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3>Recevoir un titre</h3>\n<p>Le personage doit avoir un&nbsp;renom de 5+&nbsp;et aucun titre dans la r&eacute;gion,&nbsp;co&ucirc;te 20 pi&egrave;ces d'or.</p>\n<p>Procure +1 de renom et le personage re&ccedil;oit une exploitation (holding) appropri&eacute;e.</p>\n<h2>&Eacute;v&eacute;nements (events)</h2>\n<h3>Solo</h3>\n<p>Lorsque vous &ecirc;tes en solo, roulez sur la table d'&eacute;v&eacute;nements de festoiement&nbsp;(Core p.295).</p>\n<h3>Groupe</h3>\n<p>Dans le cas o&ugrave; vous &ecirc;tes restez en groupe, lancer un&nbsp;D20 par joueur et faites la somme des 2 d&eacute;s les plus bas&nbsp;et prenez l'entr&eacute;e de la table d'&eacute;v&eacute;nements</p>\n<h2>Regroupement (regroup)</h2>\n<p>Si le groupe &agrave; &eacute;t&eacute; s&eacute;par&eacute; ou divis&eacute;, vous devez trouver une raison pour vous rassembl&eacute; et continuer l'aventure ensemble.</p>"}
{"_id":"Uyjl6lKuTW3mtSY3","name":"Poisoned","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"fitw9XwkJ1H7s1wk","sort":600001,"flags":{},"content":"<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">While each poison has a specific effect, the general effect is to grant the character the Staggered condition.</p>"}
{"_id":"ZHwm6Uz3hfozRKYn","name":"Spending Experience","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"b3GqfKX5F9CV6QNC","sort":800001,"flags":{},"content":"<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<h2>Am&eacute;lioration d'attributs</h2>\n<p>L'augmentation d'un point d'attribut co&ucirc;te [100xp X nouveau niveau de l'attribut].</p>\n<p>Maximum de 14 points dans un attribut.</p>\n<h2>Am&eacute;lioration de l'Expertise et du Focus</h2>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Co&ucirc;t en XP</td>\n<td>Am&eacute;lioration de l'Expertise</td>\n<td>Am&eacute;lioration du Focus</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>200</td>\n<td>0&nbsp;=&gt;&nbsp;+1</td>\n<td>0&nbsp;=&gt;&nbsp;1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>400</td>\n<td>+1&nbsp;=&gt;&nbsp;+2</td>\n<td>1&nbsp;=&gt;&nbsp;1-2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>600</td>\n<td>+2&nbsp;=&gt;&nbsp;+3</td>\n<td>1-2&nbsp;=&gt;&nbsp;1-3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>800</td>\n<td>+3&nbsp;=&gt;&nbsp;+4</td>\n<td>1-3&nbsp;=&gt;&nbsp;1-4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1000</td>\n<td>+4&nbsp;=&gt;&nbsp;+5</td>\n<td>1-4&nbsp;=&gt;&nbsp;1-5</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Achat de Talents</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>1er talent de chaque arbre: 200 xp</li>\n<li>Talents suivants: 200 xp pour niveau de distance du premier talent. (Chaque fl&egrave;che compte pour un niveau.)</li>\n<li>Rabais: Pour chaque point de focus dans la comp&eacute;tence correspondante, -25xp</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n</div>"}
{"_id":"dUuacdKxMM6XSiTD","name":"Dangers & Hazards","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"I7kECt96x9WDlEKq","sort":100001,"flags":{},"content":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 135px;\">Effect<br />(Damage or Quality)</th>\n<th style=\"width: 135px;\">Doom Cost</th>\n<th style=\"width: 426px;\">Examples</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">2&sect;damage</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">The player character stands on a sharpened spike or takes a punch from behind.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">3&sect;damage</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">A booby-trap constructed from small sharp blades; spears that spring from the walls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">4&sect;damage</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">A hidden man-trap; small rockslide.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">5&sect;damage</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">5</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">A more lethal trap; a mid-sized rockslide.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">6&sect;damage</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">6</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">A large and deadly trap; a large rockslide.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Area</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">A complicated trap that fres multiple darts or stones.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Incendiary X</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Equal to half X, rounding up</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">A fre spreads around the player character; the roof catches fre and<br />starts to cave in; molten lava in close proximity.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Intense</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">A massive boulder; a sharpened man-trap.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Knockdown</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">A log swung at shoulder height; a small pitfall.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Nonlethal</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Reduce overall Doom Cost by two</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">A sand dune collapsing on the player character; a fall onto soft ground.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Piercing X</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Equal to half X, rounding up.</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">Sharpened stakes or rocks.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Stun</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">A gas stirred up by the opening of ancient doors; a trap that drops rocks.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Persistent X</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Equal to half X, rounding up</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">Long narrow blades that leave bleeding wounds.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Vicious X</td>\n<td style=\"width: 133px;\">Equal to X</td>\n<td style=\"width: 424px;\">Traps set by master trap makers.<br /><br /></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Falling</h2>\n<p>A common form of hazard is falling. The distance a character falls determines falling damage.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Falling a Close distance inflicts 2&sect; in physical damage and carries the Stun Quality.</li>\n<li>Falling a Medium distance inflicts 4&sect; in physical damage and carries the Stun Quality.</li>\n<li>Falling a Long distance inflicts 6&sect; in physical damage and carries both the Stun and Vicious 1 Qualities.</li>\n<li>Falling an Extreme distance inflicts 8&sect; in physical damage carrying both the Stun and Vicious 1 Qualities.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>A falling character may attempt an Average (D1) Acrobatics test to reduce this damage, gaining 1 additional point of Armor Soak against the falling damage. Momentum may be spent to increase this Soak by 1 for each point expended (Repeatable).</p>\n<h2>Drowning and Suffocation</h2>\n<p>When deprived of air for more than a few moments (such as a failed swimming test), a player character must attempt a Resistance test, once per turn, with Difficulty equal to 1 plus the number of turns since the character was last able to breathe freely, so that the first turn is Average (D1), the second is Challenging (D2), etc.&nbsp;The Born Swimmer talent applies to this test.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Success prevents any ill effects and grants a moment&rsquo;s reprieve.</li>\n<li>Failure inflicts Fatigue equal to the Difficulty of the test, before further modifiers.</li>\n<li>A successful swimming test re-sets the Difficulty to Average (D1) once more.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Characters that fall unconscious while suffocating suffer 1 Wound each turn until removed from the water and revived through a successful Challenging (D2) Healing test.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"dwHdW8uT5hj3WbiG","name":"Spellcasting","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"b3GqfKX5F9CV6QNC","sort":400001,"flags":{},"content":"<h1>Casting for Effect</h1>\n<p><em>The simplest form of spell casting in 2d20 looks like this and is known as&nbsp;Casting for Effect.</em></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Resolve - Check and make sure you have enough resolve to cast the spell.</li>\n<li>Minor action - Focus action (skipping this causes complications on a 19 or 20).</li>\n<li>Standard action - Skill test against sorcery.</li>\n<li>Complications - Any failed rolls result in a complication. Rolling a complication causes 2 complications.</li>\n<li>Momentum - On a successful test send and additional momentum you have on stronger effects.</li>\n<li>Resolve - Reduce your resolve</li>\n</ol>\n<h1>Testing for Consequences</h1>\n<p><em>The second form of casting is known as&nbsp;Testing for Consequences&nbsp;or sometimes called&nbsp;Casting for Consequence. This is not at alternate rule, but it is up to the GM to allow it on a case by case basis. Basically the idea is that the spell always goes off and you are just testing to check for it's negative effects, think of it as&nbsp;Casting to Determine Complications.</em></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Resolve - Check and make sure you have enough resolve to cast the spell.</li>\n<li>Difficulty - Determine the difficulty of the spell. Most start with a base of D1, and each momentum spend you add, adds a level of difficulty.</li>\n<li>Minor action - Focus action (skipping this causes complications on a 19 or 20).</li>\n<li>Standard action - Skill text against your spells difficulty.</li>\n<li>Complications - Each difference between the number of successes you roll vs the difficulty of the spell causes a complication. ie if you roll 3 successes on a D5 spell, you gain 2 complications.</li>\n<li>Complications - It is POSSIBLE that a failed skill test here still causes a complication as well. There is nothing specifically that says it doesn't.</li>\n<li>Complications - Rolling a 20 causes a complication.</li>\n<li>Momentum - Spend momentum as normal.</li>\n<li>Resolve - Reduce your resolve.</li>\n</ol>"}
{"_id":"l80fB7UvcevIzkNy","name":"Hindered","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"fitw9XwkJ1H7s1wk","sort":500001,"flags":{},"content":"<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">Cannot attempt any movement as a Free Acton;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">May only move within Close range (1 area away) as a Minor Acton, and only within Medium range (2 area away) as a Standard Acton;</p>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">+1 Difficulty of all terrain tests</p>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"sddjZHrtvfIUMqvU","name":"Conditions Test","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"b3GqfKX5F9CV6QNC","sort":100001,"flags":{},"content":"<h2 style=\"box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 36px; color: #333333; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 24px; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Blind</h2>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: content-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">3[CD] mental damage; +2 Difficulty to any skill test reliant on vision (normally Observation, Insight, Ranged Weapons, Sailing, etc.)</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: content-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 36px; color: #333333; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 24px; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Burning X</h2>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: content-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">Condition lasts for a number of rounds equal to number of Effects rolled (if no effects were rolled, the cause of the burning effect will list a duration); at the end of the target’s turn, X? physical and mental damage (roll once and apply it to both), ignoring Armor Soak (Effects rolled increase the number of rounds); Clear Minor Acton to remove this effect (prone character can spend a Standard Acton rolling around, and reduces the Difficulty by 2)</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: content-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 36px; color: #333333; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 24px; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Dazed</h2>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: content-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">+1 Difficulty to all skill tests until the Dazed condition ends</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: content-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 36px; color: #333333; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 24px; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Deaf</h2>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: content-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">3[CD] mental damage; +2 Difficulty to any skill test reliant on hearing (normally Observation, Insight, Command, Persuade, etc.)</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: content-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 36px; color: #333333; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 24px; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Hindered</h2>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: content-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">Cannot attempt any movement as a Free Acton; may only move within Close range (1 area away) as a Minor Acton, and only within Medium range (2 area away) as a Standard Acton; +1 Difficulty of all terrain tests</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: content-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 36px; color: #333333; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 24px; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Poisoned</h2>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: content-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">While each poison has a specific effect, the general effect is to grant the character the Staggered condition.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: content-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: content-box; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 36px; color: #333333; margin-bottom: 0px; font-size: 24px; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Staggered</h2>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: content-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px;\">Can only perform a Standard Acton in a turn if the player is willing to pay 1 point of Doom; cannot perform a Reaction unless spending 1 Fortune point in addition to the reaction’s normal Doom cost.</p>"}
{"_id":"wItzSWwq0cFWwBoL","name":"Tests ","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"I7kECt96x9WDlEKq","sort":200001,"flags":{},"content":"<h2>Test Difficulty</h2>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<td>Name</td>\n<td>Successes</td>\n<td>Examples</td>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Simple <br /><br />(D0)</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Opening a slightly stuck door.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Researching a widely known subject.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Hitting a stationary archery target during practice.</span></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Average <br /><br />(D1)</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Overcoming a simple lock. </span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Researching a specialist subject.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Shooting an enemy at optimal (medium) range.</span>&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Challenging <br /><br />(D2)</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Overcoming a complex lock.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Researching obscure information.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Shooting an enemy at optimal range in poor light.</span>&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Daunting <br /><br />(D3)</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Overcoming a complex lock in a hurry.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Researching basic historical information.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Shooting an enemy at long range in poor light.</span></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dire <br /><br />(D4)</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Overcoming a complex lock in a hurry, without the proper tools.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Researching esoteric historical information.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Shooting an enemy at long range, in poor light and heavy rain</span>.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Epic <br /><br />(D5)</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Overcoming a complex lock in a hurry, without the proper tools, and in the middle of a battle.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Researching purposefully obscured historical information.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Shooting an enemy at extreme range in poor light and heavy rain.</span> &nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Difficulty Modifiers</h2>\n<table style=\"height: 476px;\" border=\"1\">\n<thead>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 100px;\">Condition</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 591px;\">Effect</td>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 100px;\">Combinations</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 591px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If there are multiple elements that individually are not enough to warrant a penalty, the combination of conditions can collectively increase Difficulty by one step</span> &nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 119px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 119px; width: 100px;\">Lighting</td>\n<td style=\"height: 119px; width: 591px;\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Increasingly dark conditions impose progressively higher difficulties to Observation tests and other tests reliant on sight. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A bright, moonlit night may increase Difficulty by one step, a cloudy night by two steps, and complete darkness by three steps. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Conversely, extremely bright light, or moving from an area of darkness into bright light (or vice versa) can impose increased difficulties. Bright light can impose similar Difficulty increases to Stealth tests.</span> &nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 85px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 85px; width: 100px;\">Difficult Terrain</td>\n<td style=\"height: 85px; width: 591px;\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Slippery floors, sheer surfaces, deep snow, dense foliage, heaps of refuse, or even dense crowds all make movement-related tests more difficult. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">At the gamemaster&rsquo;s discretion, difficult terrain conditions can increase the Difficulty of movement-related tests, or even require a test where none would normally be required.</span> &nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 100px;\">Disruption or Distraction</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 591px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The interference of hostile creatures or characters may impose an increased Difficulty, depending on the severity of the interference.</span> &nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 100px;\">Distance</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 591px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If a skill is usable at a distance, every range category beyond Close increases Difficulty by one step.</span> &nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 100px;\">Equipment</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 591px;\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A character performing a task without the proper tools increases the Difficulty by one step. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">In some cases, performing a skill test outside of a proper environment (a workshop, laboratory, archive, etc.) may increase the Difficulty by one step as well, but, if failed, the test can be retried within that environment later on.</span> &nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 100px;\">Foreign Language</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 591px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Any social test in which the character does not speak the language fluently has the Difficulty increased by one step.</span> &nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 100px;\">Noise</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 591px;\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Loud noises can hinder a character&rsquo;s attempts to be heard or to hear other noises. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Moderate noise (such as a crowd) increases Difficulty by one step. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Loud noise (an angry mob, a battle) increases Difficulty by two steps.</span> &nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 100px;\">Poor Weather</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 591px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A character exposed to severe weather (wind, rain, snow, fog, etc.) may face an increase in Difficulty by one step.</span> &nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 100px;\">Random Motion</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 591px;\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Being on a galloping horse, strong winds, crashing waves, and the like are often enough to hinder a test. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Skills relying on concentration or a controlled environment increase Difficulty by one step when used in an environment of random motion, such as a ship in choppy waters.</span> &nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 100px;\">Social Factors</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 591px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Social tests when interacting with a character that does not trust you, who is of a rival faction, or who thinks you have committed some slight or social faux pas, increase in Difficulty by one or more steps, at the gamemaster&rsquo;s discretion.</span> &nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 100px;\">Unfamiliarity or Complexity</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px; width: 591px;\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Performing complex or specialized tasks, or tasks in which the character has little experience, increases the Difficulty. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This is subject to gamemaster&rsquo;s discretion and varies by situation and conditions. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">For example, a Cimmerian village healer may have little experience with Stygian poisons, while an Aquilonian alchemist may struggle when confronted with a text from ancient Acheron.</span> &nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"}
{"_id":"y6dK4qajdKJI7tu8","name":"Fortune Points","permission":{"default":0,"TnWyDcFgUQWxXpUx":3},"folder":"b3GqfKX5F9CV6QNC","sort":300001,"flags":{},"content":"<h1>Spend Fortune to:</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Add a d20 on a result of &laquo; 1 &raquo; (Fortune spent before the roll)</li>\n<li>Perform an additional Standard Action</li>\n<li>Restore one Stress (Vigor or Resolve) to full</li>\n<li>Ignore all instances of a single Harm type until the end of the current Scene</li>\n<li>Influence the Story</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Regain Fortune from (max 5):</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Start of session (3 or 2) or an hour of play (1-3)</li>\n<li>Good roleplaying (1)</li>\n<li>Voluntary Failure (1 Doom Point + 1&nbsp;Fortune Point)</li>\n<li>Creating a Complication with a Trait&nbsp;of the character (1) &nbsp;</li>\n</ul>"}
